shared_text:
Neshoba County School District
August 7 at 4:10 PM Â·

Congratulations to our students and staff on an outstanding first week of school!

Car Rider Line- We know the line is very long at this time. In an attempt to possibly alleviate congestion, if you have an NCMS and NCHS student to drop off, please take St. Francis Dr. from the hospital to enter the middle/high school line if at all possible.

Outstanding job by our staff and students on our new safety protocols! Let's stay healthy!

Reminder- If you are under quarantine, awaiting Covid test results, or have tested positive, please contact the school to let them know. DO NOT COME TO SCHOOL if you or your family is under quarantine. Please remember, if you come to school under these circumstances you will be sent to alternative school or possibly expelled. The safety and health of our staff and students is paramount.

On Monday, August 10, a technology survey will be sent home to each student. These should be returned by Wednesday, August 12.

#OneCommunity #OneMission #OneNeshoba

Congratulations to our students and staff on an outstanding first week of school!

Car Rider Line- We know the line is very long at this time. In an attempt to possibly alleviate congestion, if you have an NCMS and NCHS student to drop off, please take St. Francis Dr. from the hospital to enter the middle/high school line if at all possible.

Outstanding job by our staff and students on our new safety protocols! Let's stay healthy!

Reminder- If you are under quarantine, awaiting Covid test results, or have tested positive, please contact the school to let them know. DO NOT COME TO SCHOOL if you or your family is under quarantine. Please remember, if you come to school under these circumstances you will be sent to alternative school or possibly expelled. #OneCommunity #OneMission #OneNeshoba

Neshoba County School District
April 20 at 12:59 PM Â·

Important Information:

â€¢ The NCSD is continuing to offer educational opportunities until the end of the semester in May.
â€¢ Report cards will be issued at the normal time when school is out in May.
â€¢ Grades for the year will be as follows: 1st Semester- 67% 2nd Semester- 33%
Example 1â€¦1st semester average is 80 and 3rd 9-weeks grade is 95.
80 x .67 = 53.6
95 x .33 = 31.35
53.6 + 31.35 = 84.95 or 85
Example 2â€¦1st semester average is 63 and 3rd 9 weeks is 72.
63 x .67 = 42.21
72 x .33 = 23.76
42.21 + 23.76 = 65.97 or 66
Classes at NCHS and NCMS that meet for one (1) semester, the 3rd 9-week grade will also be the final grade.
â€¢ Dual Credit classes are calculated as normal.
â€¢ If you have questions about this process and/or your childâ€™s progress, please email the principal of the school your child attends.
#OneCommunity #OneMission #OneNeshoba
